# Handoff checklist (mandatory before handoff)

When the user wants a handoff, or when you are writing or updating a handoff note (e.g. **`doc/handoff/HANDOFF-*.md`** or **`.cursor/handoff/handoff-*.md`** — both **gitignored**, not on **`main`**):

## When to create a handoff (timing)

- **Right time:** You are at a real stopping point: scope is done **or** you are intentionally handing off **mid-flight** with a clear label (e.g. **WIP**, **blocked**, **needs decision**).
- **Wrong time:** Do **not** write a handoff that reads “ship complete” if delivery is not actually finished (e.g. commits on `main` that were never pushed, CI not run, or known follow-ups omitted). If work is incomplete, **say so explicitly** in **Ship status** or a **Not done** section at the top — not only in **Next up**.
- **Push:** When `npm run ci` is green and you committed to **`main`**, run **`git push origin main`** before ending unless the user asked you not to push, or push failed (then record the failure and that **`main` is ahead of origin**).

**You must run all four and record results in the handoff note. Do not skip any.**

1. **Code review** — Use the **code-reviewer** skill (`.cursor/skills/code-reviewer/SKILL.md`). Review the changed or relevant code since last handoff (or main branch). Output PASS/WARN/FAIL and a short summary. Put the summary in the handoff note under **Code review**.
2. **Tech debt evaluation** — Use the **tech-debt-evaluator** skill (`.cursor/skills/tech-debt-evaluator/SKILL.md`). Assess current debt; produce prioritized list. Put the short summary or "Do first" items in the handoff note under **Tech debt**.
3. **Tests / coverage** — Run **`npm run ci`** (or the documented commands in **AGENT_HANDOFF.md** / **TEST_PLAN.md**). Note whether Tier 1 is green and, if useful, a one-line summary. Put in the handoff note under **Code coverage** (or **Tests**).
4. **Project readiness (optional)** — If you maintain a readiness checklist or skill for this product, use it and put the summary under **Project readiness**. Otherwise note "N/A" or skip that section.

5. **Tier 2 (integration / E2E) if needed** — If you added or changed behavior that requires integration or E2E validation, run the Tier 2 command from TEST_PLAN.md. Note in the handoff whether Tier 2 was run and the result. See `.cursor/rules/testing.mdc` and TEST_PLAN.md.

6. **Git commit + push** — If the first four checks passed: stage the changes and run `git commit` with a short message. **`git push origin main`** (or merge your branch into `main` then push) after **`npm run ci`** is green — see **AGENT_HANDOFF.md** → *Git workflow*. Treat “committed but not pushed” as **unfinished** unless the user asked to stop before push.

Then complete the rest of the handoff (update **PM_PLAN** / **EDGE plan** if product scope changed; **Done this session**, **Next up**, etc. in your **`doc/handoff/`** or `.cursor/handoff/` note — see **AGENT_HANDOFF.md**).

**Filename and timestamp:** Prefer **`doc/handoff/HANDOFF-YYYY-MM-DD-HHmmss.md`** (local **24h** time, no colons — Windows-safe) so multiple handoffs per day get unique files. Add a **`Recorded:`** line under the H1 (ISO-8601 or local offset). See **AGENT_HANDOFF.md** → Source of truth → session notes.
